PROFILE

Information Technology graduate with foundations in web technologies, database systems and cloud services. Highly motivated and eager to learn, with a strong work ethic and solid communication skills developed through customer-facing experience and industry-based projects. Seeking an entry-level opportunity to develop my skills and grow within the technology support domain.
EDUCATION & QUALIFICATIONS
RMIT - Bachelor`s degree Information Technology  Graduated 2025
Microsoft Certified Azure Fundamentals (AZ-900) Completed 2026
KEY SKILLS
Proven ability to collaborate in cross-functional academic and operational teams to deliver projects and meet performance targets.
Applied structured problem-solving to identify, assess, and resolve technical issues.
Documented incidents and technical processes clearly for non-technical stakeholders
Adapted quickly to new environments by working across multiple agencies and managing concurrent responsibilities efficiently.
Followed established procedures and escalated issues appropriately when required
Technical Skills:
Programming and Scripting: Python, SQL Java, JavaScript, PowerShell
Web Development and Frameworks: HTML, CSS, UI/UX Design, Bootstrap 5
Version Control and Best Practices: Git, Agile/Scrum methodology, User Stories, Kanban, etc
PROFESSIONAL PROJECTS
VAMBAT – Visualisation platform for advanced biodiversity monitoring (WIL placement)
Collaborated with cross-functional teams to process IOT-generated CSV data into a visual dashboard and provided clear user guidance and documentation to support non-technical users.
Troubleshot application, database and connectivity issues across PostgreSQL, Node-RED and Grafana to restore normal functionality for team members.
Deployed and configured a Docker based application stack, ensuring services run reliably by monitoring logs and ingestion metrics to identify and resolve data processing issues
Create clear and detailed setup and troubleshooting documentation to assist users and support future development and maintenance.
VetCARE – Online Veterinary Clinic Management System (Team Lead)
Served as Team Lead and coordinated sprint deliverables and assisted in troubleshooting backend and frontend issues to ensure stable system functions and timely project completion.
Troubleshot backend and database connectivity issues for team members to ensure system functionality and minimal disruptions to the workflow during development.
Conducted user testing with non-technical users, monitoring system interaction to identify usability issues and gather feedback for further improvements.
Acted as the primary liaison between the development team and product owner, facilitating sprint meetings and clarifying technical requirements.
WORK EXPERIENCE
Warehouse Pick Packer | Premier Fresh (Fresh Produce Warehouse)Jun 2025 to Feb 2026
One of Australia´s largest fresh produce supply chain companies, distributing fresh fruit and vegetables to customers worldwide
Worked in a fast-paced, process driven warehouse environment to ensure produce is repacked accurately and consistently according to the Value-Added Batch receipts provided by clients.
Applied technical troubleshooting skills to teach others how to operate and maintain label printers to minimise workflow disruptions
Followed established procedures and deferred issues to others when necessary to maintain workflow efficiency
Mobile Patrol Officer | SOS SecurityAug 2022 to Nov 2024
SOS provides ethical security services while also creating pathways to employment for disadvantaged members of the community
Responded to incidents on a constructions site and assessed situation using structured problem solving to determine appropriate action
Conducted routine inspections and documented incidents in detailed reports and communication updates to clients and other relevant stakeholders
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
Training – Currently studying to get Azure Administrator Associate (AZ-104)
Languages – Hindi; Urdu
INTERESTS

Competitive esports player (in-game leader responsible for team coordination and decision-making under pressure) and club cricket (former team captain, demonstrating leadership and teamwork). Interested in technology trends and continuous skill development, specifically PC hardware and currently learning software development.
